The paper deals with equalization and decoding in the presence of ISI channels, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed graph representation is a form of graphical model, which is a common tool in statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of linear programming and iterative message-passing decoding algorithms, which are relevant to optimization (cs.DS).
